      "translations": {
        "en.mulla-asgharali-m-m-jaffer": {
          "segments": [
            "42. And with the former chain of narration from ‘Ali ibn Mahzyar, from Fadhalah, from Ismail from Abu Abdillah, peace be upon him, who said: Amirul Mu’mineen (as) used to say: \"Awaken your heart by reflection and let your side forsake (long) sleep, and fear Allah, your Sustainer (by guarding against sins and evil).\""
          ],
          "text": "42. And with the former chain of narration from ‘Ali ibn Mahzyar, from Fadhalah, from Ismail from Abu Abdillah, peace be upon him, who said: Amirul Mu’mineen (as) used to say: \"Awaken your heart by reflection and let your side forsake (long) sleep, and fear Allah, your Sustainer (by guarding against sins and evil).\""
        }
